    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-08-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-08-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="619"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d619">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">860c.24/61</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Poland</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stetson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-08-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 16, 1927</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 453</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to your confidential despatch No.
                    1163 of July 14, 1927, requesting instructions regarding the assistance to be
                    rendered to American companies interested in negotiating for a contract <pb
                        facs="0709" n="607" xml:id="pg_607"/> with the Polish Government for the
                    sale of arms, the Department, in the circumstances, desires that if approached
                    in the premises by any other company, you request instructions of the Department
                    as was done in the Legation’s telegram No. 7, January 22, 11 a.m., with respect
                    to Colt’s Patent Firearms Manufacturing Company.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. R. Castle</hi>, Jr.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
